---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — Guitar Tab Reader" description="Terms of service for the Guitar Tab Reader app.">
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: June 22, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">By downloading or using Guitar Tab Reader ("the app"), you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, do not use the app.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Guitar Tab Reader is a free application for opening, viewing, and playing back Guitar Pro and tablature files. It renders tab and standard notation, provides multi-track audio playback, and includes practice tools such as tempo control and looping.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Free to Use</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The app is provided free of charge. There are no accounts, subscriptions, in-app purchases, or paid features.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Your Content</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">You are responsible for the files you open with the app and for ensuring you have the right to use them. The app processes your files locally on your device; we do not receive, store, or claim any rights to your content.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The app itself, including its name and visual design, is owned by its developer. Guitar Pro is a trademark of its respective owner; Guitar Tab Reader is an independent reader and is not affiliated with or endorsed by Arobas Music.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>Reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble the app, except where permitted by law.</li>
          <li>Use the app for any unlawful purpose.</li>
          <li>Use the app to infringe the intellectual property rights of others.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Disclaimers</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The app is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We do not guarantee that every file will render or play back perfectly, or that the app will operate without interruption or errors.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">To the maximum extent permitted by law, Guitar Tab Reader and its developer shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the app.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">We may revise these terms at any time. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Questions about these terms? Reach us at <a href="mailto:support@guitartabreader.app" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">support@guitartabreader.app</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
